The paper proposes a deep learning structure for sequential labeling problems, which involves learning discriminative features and incorporating context information from sequential data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
